FBIS4-23489 "drafr109_c_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA North-West Premier Molefe Admitted to Hospital North-West Premier Molefe Admitted to Hospital MB0606185794 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1834 GMT 6 Jun 94 MB0606185794 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] Mmabatho June 6 SAPA -- North-West Premier Mr Popo Molefe was on Monday [6 June] morning "admitted" because of ill health, his office said in a brief statement. Asked to elaborate, office head Mr Martin Mabiletsa refused "for reasons of security" to give further details such as the state of Mr Molefe's health or to which institution he had been admitted. Provincial Minister of Police Mr Satish Roopa has been appointed acting premier.
